# Validation Guide

## Using hamr/pkg/validate

All validators return `""` for valid input or an error message string for invalid input.

### Available Validators

```go
validate.Required(value)          // "This field is required"
validate.Email(value)             // "Invalid email address"
validate.MinLength(value, 8)      // "Must be at least 8 characters"
validate.MaxLength(value, 100)    // "Must be at most 100 characters"
validate.PasswordStrength(value)  // Checks upper, lower, digit, special, length
validate.URL(value)               // "Invalid URL"
validate.Phone(value)             // "Invalid phone number"
validate.OneOf(value, "a", "b")   // "Must be one of: a, b"
```

### Custom Error Messages

Every validator has a `*Msg` variant:

```go
validate.RequiredMsg(value, "Please enter your name")
validate.EmailMsg(value, "That doesn't look like an email")
```

## Validation Pattern

### 1. Define validation in handler

```go
func validateForm(email, password string) map[string]string {
    errs := make(map[string]string)
    if msg := validate.Required(email); msg != "" {
        errs["email"] = msg
    }
    if msg := validate.Email(email); msg != "" {
        errs["email"] = msg
    }
    if msg := validate.PasswordStrength(password); msg != "" {
        errs["password"] = msg
    }
    return errs
}
```

### 2. Return validation errors

```go
errs := validateForm(email, password)
if len(errs) > 0 {
    return respond.ValidationError(c, errs, FormWithErrors(errs))
}
```

### 3. Single-field validation (HTMX blur)

Create a `POST /validate/<field>` endpoint that validates one field and returns
an OOB swap for the error element:

```go
// POST /validate/email
func (h *Handler) ValidateEmail(c echo.Context) error {
    email := c.FormValue("email")
    msg := validate.Email(email)
    return respond.HTML(c, http.StatusOK, form.FieldErrorOOB("email", msg))
}
```

## Custom Validators

```go
validate.Register("slug", func(v string) string {
    if !regexp.MustCompile(`^[a-z0-9-]+$`).MatchString(v) {
        return "Must contain only lowercase letters, numbers, and hyphens"
    }
    return ""
})

// Usage:
msg := validate.Run("slug", value)
```
